% You are an expert Python engineer. Your goal is to implement
% `pdd/story_regression.py`, the deterministic, marker-traceable pytest
% story↔test traceability foundation for PDD.

<include>context/python_preamble.prompt</include>

% Role & Scope
Implement the **deterministic, runnable-pytest** oracle that links a user story
(`user_stories/story__<slug>.md`) to the pytest regression tests that claim it via
the `@pytest.mark.story` marker. This module performs **collection only** — it
never runs an LLM, never executes test bodies, and never triggers `e2e`/`real`
collection side effects.

It is intentionally separate from the LLM oracle in `pdd/user_story_tests.py`:
that module links stories to *prompts* and validates them with `detect_change`
(an LLM call). This module is a *deterministic* story↔test map. The only shared
concept is the `story_id` identity, which is reused from `user_story_tests`'s
public `story_id` helper so both systems share one identity space.

% Requirements
1. **One identity space.** Reuse the public `story_id` helper exposed by
   `.user_story_tests` (`story__<slug>.md` -> `<slug>`) as the single `story_id`
   convention. Do NOT introduce a second slug convention.
2. **Build the bidirectional map by collection, not execution.** Construct the
   `story_id <-> {nodeid}` map with a `pytest --collect-only` plugin —
   e.g. `pytest.main(["--collect-only", "-q", str(tests_dir)], plugins=[collector])`
   with a `pytest_collection_modifyitems` hook that records `item.nodeid` against
   the story ids read from `item.iter_markers(name="story")`. Scope collection to
   the `tests/` tree.
3. **Accept both marker forms.** Normalize `@pytest.mark.story(story_id="x")`
   (keyword) and `@pytest.mark.story("x")` (positional `args[0]`) to one resolved
   `story_id`. Marker values may be either canonical ids (`foo_flow`) or story
   file references (`user_stories/story__foo_flow.md`); both normalize through
   the shared `story_id` helper.
4. **Two resolvers over one map.** Expose `tests_for_story(story_id) -> set[str]`
   (node ids that claim the story) and `story_for_test(nodeid)` returning the
   owning story id(s) (a test may claim more than one story). Both directions MUST
   be backed by the **same** collected map so they cannot drift.
5. **Cardinality.** Support one story -> many tests and one test -> >=1 story
   (`iter_markers` yields one `Mark` per decorator application).
6. **Orphan detection (both directions).** Detect a `story_id` with no claiming
   test, and a marker referencing a `story_id` with no matching
   `story__<slug>.md` (surface the latter as a validation warning, distinct from
   the no-test gap).
7. **Coverage predicate.** Provide `has_regression_test(story_id) -> bool` (true
   when >=1 collected test claims the story) for `coverage_contracts` to consume.
8. **MUST NOT:** invoke an LLM, execute test bodies, or trigger `e2e`/`real`
   collection side effects — rely on `--collect-only`.
9. **Graceful degradation.** If a test module is unparseable, skip it and continue
   rather than crashing; an absent `tests/` directory yields an empty map without
   error.

% Inputs and Outputs
- `story_id(path) -> str` — re-exported/reused from `.user_story_tests`.
- `tests_for_story(story_ref: str | Path) -> set[str]` — node ids claiming the
  story; accepts either a canonical id or a `story__*.md` path.
- `story_for_test(nodeid: str) -> str | set[str] | None` — owning story id(s).
- `has_regression_test(story_ref: str | Path) -> bool` — convenience predicate.
- Node ids emitted by the map MUST be stable relative ids under the collected
  tests root (for example `test_story.py::test_case`), not machine-specific
  absolute temp paths.
- Orphan diagnostics (stories with no test; markers naming a nonexistent story).

% Dependencies
<pdd.user_story_tests><include>context/user_story_tests_example.py</include></pdd.user_story_tests>
- `pytest` — used purely for `--collect-only` collection (a `pytest_collection_modifyitems` plugin).

% Deliverables
- Code: `pdd/story_regression.py`
- Exports: `story_id`, `tests_for_story`, `story_for_test`, `has_regression_test`

% Verification
```bash
pytest -q tests/test_story_regression.py
pylint pdd/story_regression.py
```
